data.enText: a thick solid piece that has been cut or broken off sth

data.chText: 一块厚厚的奶酪 / 砖石

data.enText: a fairly large amount of sth

data.chText: 我已写出文章的大部分。
data.enText: I've already written a fair chunk of the article.
a phrase or group of words which can be learnt as a unit by sb who is learning a language. Examples of chunks are ‘Can I have the bill, please?’ and ‘Pleased to meet you’.

example: a ball of mud caught him on the shoulder
we won a chunk of money

tr: group or chunk together in a certain order or place side by side

value.def: Chunks of something are thick solid pieces of it.

example.ex: They had to be careful of floating chunks of ice.
example.tran: 他们必须当心大块浮冰。

value.def: A chunk of something is a large amount or large part of it.

example.ex: The company owns a chunk of farmland near Gatwick Airport.
example.tran: 该公司拥有盖特威克机场周边的大片农田。
